Movie Description 
A cult of zombie creatures threaten the entire human race. Jack Deth, defender of justice and Trancer-hunter, is the only man who can save Earth. 

Credits 
Cast: Helen Hunt, Tim Thomerson 
Director: Charles Band 

Synopsis 
Angel City trooper Jack Deth is sent back in time, to 1985 Los Angeles, to inhabit the body of his ancestor. Deth&#039;s assignment is to find his arch-enemy, Whistler, who turns people into zombies, before Whistler is able to kill all the ancestors of the members of the governing council. 

Film Notes 
A low-rent "Bladerunner" with a little time travel from "The Terminator" thrown in. Still, as it never takes itself too seriously, it&#039;s kind of fun. And even in the future, they don&#039;t know how to pronounce "Cahuenga." 
Trancers 2 Movie Description 
Los Angeles, 1991. It&#039;s been six years since Jack Deth, a cop from the future, wiped out the last of the Trancers, those zombie-like creatures whose mission is murder. Now Jack&#039;s got that funny feeling again...He knows they&#039;re back. And he&#039;s ready to give them the fight of his life. 

Credits 
Cast: Tim Thomerson 
Director: Charles Band 
Trancers 3-Movie Description 
Time-traveling cop Jack Deth is sent to the year 2005 to fight the deadliest form of Trancer ever. The new government developed Trancers to combine the power they&#039;ve always had with a new weapon. A brain and the tougher-than-ever Jack Deth could be their next recruit. 

Credits 
Cast: Tim Thomerson 
Director: C. Courtney Joyner 

Trancers-4-Movie Description
